The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to graphs and their structures, which are typically studied in computer science sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The problem of finding a connected vertex cover is a classic graph problem that falls under these sub-categories. The paper's focus on parameterized algorithms and its use of techniques such as dynamic programming and branching suggest that it is likely to be classified under these sub-categories.
